responses.answer:
Both pass data from parent → child components, but input() is the modern signal-based API:

@Input() (classic) — uses decorator, returns plain value
input() (Angular 17+) — returns a Signal, fully reactive

Similarly for outputs:
@Output() + EventEmitter (classic)
output() (Angular 17+) — cleaner, no EventEmitter needed

